### Test the root endpoint
GET http://localhost:8000/

### Calculate NDVI
# This endpoint returns a multipart response with both metadata and the image file
POST http://localhost:8000/calculate/NDVI > ndvi_response.json
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="image.tif"
Content-Type: image/tiff

< ./image.tif
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="metadata"

{"redBand": 1, "nirBand": 2}
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

>
# The response contains:
# 1. Metadata as JSON (processing time, statistics, etc.)
# 2. The processed image file
#
# To save the response to a file:
# GET http://localhost:8000/calculate/NDVI > ndvi_response.json
# Or for just the image:
# GET http://localhost:8000/download/filename.png > saved_image.png
# You can save the response to a file using > operator or use the /download endpoint

